- label: Util
  kind: 7
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nclass Util\n```\n---\nUtility functions.\n\n### Methods\n- `base64Decode` ‚Äî `(stringToDecode: str, url: bool?): str` ‚Äî Converts a string from base64 to UTF-8.\n- `base64Encode` ‚Äî `(stringToEncode: str, url: bool?): str` ‚Äî Converts a string from UTF-8 to base64.\n- `env` ‚Äî `(name: str): str` ‚Äî Returns the value of an environment variable.\n- `exec` ‚Äî `(program: str, args: Array<str>, opts: ExecOptions?): Output` ‚Äî Execute a program with the given arguments, wait for it to finish, and return its outputs.\n- `nanoid` ‚Äî `(options: NanoidOptions?): str` ‚Äî Generates a unique ID using the nanoid library.\n- `sha256` ‚Äî `(data: str): str` ‚Äî Computes the SHA256 hash of the given data.\n- `shell` ‚Äî `(command: str, opts: ShellOptions?): str` ‚Äî Executes a command in the shell and returns its standard output.\n- `sleep` ‚Äî `(delay: duration): void` ‚Äî Suspends execution for a given duration.\n- `tryEnv` ‚Äî `(name: str): str?` ‚Äî Returns the value of an environment variable.\n- `ulid` ‚Äî `(options: UlidOptions?): str` ‚Äî Generates universally unique lexicographically sortable identifier.\n- `uuidv4` ‚Äî `(): str` ‚Äî Generates a version 4 UUID.\n- `waitUntil` ‚Äî `inflight (predicate: inflight (): bool, props: WaitUntilProps?): bool` ‚Äî Run a predicate repeatedly, waiting until it returns true or until the timeout elapses."
  sortText: gg|Util
- label: CommandOptions
  kind: 22
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nstruct CommandOptions\n```\n---\nBase command options.\n### Fields\n- `cwd?` ‚Äî `str?` ‚Äî Path to a directory to run the command in.\n- `env?` ‚Äî `Map<str>?` ‚Äî Environment variables.\n- `inheritEnv?` ‚Äî `bool?` ‚Äî Whether to inherit environment variables from the host's environment."
  sortText: hh|CommandOptions
- label: ExecOptions
  kind: 22
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nstruct ExecOptions extends CommandOptions\n```\n---\nAdditional options for `util.exec()`.\n### Fields\n- `cwd?` ‚Äî `str?`\n- `env?` ‚Äî `Map<str>?`\n- `inheritEnv?` ‚Äî `bool?`"
  sortText: hh|ExecOptions
- label: NanoidOptions
  kind: 22
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nstruct NanoidOptions\n```\n---\nOptions to generating a unique ID.\n### Fields\n- `alphabet?` ‚Äî `str?` ‚Äî Characters that make up the alphabet to generate the ID, limited to 256 characters or fewer.\n- `size?` ‚Äî `num?` ‚Äî Size of ID."
  sortText: hh|NanoidOptions
- label: Output
  kind: 22
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nstruct Output\n```\n---\nOutput of a finished process.\n### Fields\n- `status` ‚Äî `num` ‚Äî A process's exit status.\n- `stderr` ‚Äî `str` ‚Äî The standard error of a finished process.\n- `stdout` ‚Äî `str` ‚Äî The standard output of a finished process."
  sortText: hh|Output
- label: ShellOptions
  kind: 22
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nstruct ShellOptions extends CommandOptions\n```\n---\nAdditional options for `util.shell()`.\n### Fields\n- `cwd?` ‚Äî `str?`\n- `env?` ‚Äî `Map<str>?`\n- `inheritEnv?` ‚Äî `bool?`\n- `throw?` ‚Äî `bool?` ‚Äî Whether to throw an error on command execution failure."
  sortText: hh|ShellOptions
- label: UlidOptions
  kind: 22
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nstruct UlidOptions\n```\n---\nOptions to generate universally unique lexicographically sortable identifiers.\n### Fields\n- `seed?` ‚Äî `num?` ‚Äî You can also input a seed time which will consistently give you the same string for the time component."
  sortText: hh|UlidOptions
- label: WaitUntilProps
  kind: 22
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\nstruct WaitUntilProps\n```\n---\nProperties for `util.waitUntil`.\n### Fields\n- `interval?` ‚Äî `duration?` ‚Äî Interval between predicate retries.\n- `timeout?` ‚Äî `duration?` ‚Äî The timeout for keep trying predicate."
  sortText: hh|WaitUntilProps
- label: IPredicateHandler
  kind: 8
  documentation:
    kind: markdown
    value: "```wing\ninterface IPredicateHandler extends IInflight\n```\n---\nA predicate with an inflight \"handle\" method that can be passed to `util.busyWait`.\n### Methods\n- `handle` ‚Äî `inflight (): bool` ‚Äî The Predicate function that is called.\n- `onLift` ‚Äî `preflight (host: IInflightHost, ops: Array<str>): void`"
  sortText: ii|IPredicateHandler
